5000|$|In the United States, {{the pardon}} power for federal crimes is {{granted to the}} President of the United States under Article II, Section 2 of the United States Constitution which states that the President [...] "shall have power to grant reprieves and pardons for offenses against the United States, except in cases of impeachment". The U.S. Supreme Court has {{interpreted}} this language to include the power to grant pardons, conditional pardons, <b>commutations</b> <b>of</b> <b>sentence,</b> conditional <b>commutations</b> <b>of</b> <b>sentence,</b> remissions <b>of</b> fines and forfeitures, respites, and amnesties.|$|R
