50|$|In 1977, {{the first}} {{democratic}} government elected after Franco's death passed the Law 46/1977, of amnesty, which exempted {{of responsibility to}} everyone who committed any offence for political reasons prior to this date. This law allowed the <b>commutation</b> <b>of</b> <b>sentences</b> <b>of</b> those accused to attack the dictatorship and secured that those crimes committed during the Francoism would not be prosecuted.|$|R
